28/09/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- The situations in the Balkans and in the Middle East were the focus of talks between Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice and Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis on Wednesday (27 September).
Rice praised Greece's work this month as holder of the rotating UN Security Council presidency, while Bakoyannis reiterated her country's stance regarding Kosovo â namely, that any solution to the status issue must result from a compromise between the two sides.
She also said Serbia must be supported in its aspirations for Euro-Atlantic integration.
(Eleftherotypia - 28/09/06;
ANA-MPA, Naftemporiki - 27/09/06)
